Hispanic West Harlem residents are underrepresented in Columbia clinical trials.

Hispanic residents comprise 30 percent of the clinical trial participants residing in West Harlem despite accounting for 40 percent of Community Board 9’s population. Meanwhile, white residents comprise 37 percent of CUIMC clinical trial participants from West Harlem despite accounting for 25 percent of the community board’s population.
